Wilshere: &quot;On a personal note it&rsquo;s nice to get on the scoresheet. I was playing in a more central position &amp; had a bit more license to get in the box &amp; get off more shots&quot;<br />
<br />
Wilshere on not starting in the Premier League: &quot;This is #Arsenal, we have top players &amp; all I can do when I&rsquo;m called upon in the Europa League &amp; off the bench in the Premier League is give my all, but at the end of the day what matters is the team&quot;

Lacazette: &ldquo;For Mesut, it&rsquo;s about passes, his vision of the game and passes. For Alexis, perseverance. He always wants to go further, be stronger and rise higher. As well as being very fast, he always wants go even further. I already get on very well with them in every day life.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Lacazette: &ldquo;I&rsquo;m the one who has to get to know them more, rather than them as they&rsquo;ve been playing together for quite a few years. It takes time to adapt. It will take days, weeks, maybe months, I don&rsquo;t know. It&rsquo;s not a problem, but I know that in time we&rsquo;ll get on even better.&rdquo;
